content:
The InsPolicy interface is a generic service interface that lets Vlocity policy services work with any policy data model, including the Salesforce FSC Insurance Policy data model.

Vlocity Insurance policy services no longer interact with database objects and fields directly. Instead, they rely on the caller to fetch or post data to database objects and fields using Omnistudio Data Mappers or Apex classes.

Here's how Vlocity objects map to Salesforce FSC objects:

* Asset -> InsurancePolicy
* AssetCoverage__c -> InsurancePolicyCoverage
* AssetInsuredItem__c -> InsurancePolicyAsset

For InsurancePolicyAsset, an associated CustomerProperty record is required via the CustomerPropertyId field on the InsurancePolicyAsset.

Data Mappers and custom classes are provided with the Insurance Industries Extension package to use in conjunction with InsPolicyService and InsPolicyRevenueScheduleService services. These Data Mappers can be modified to fit business needs.

The following Data Mappers and custom classes are included:

* getFSCPolicyDetail
* postFSCPolicyDetailGeneric
* postVersionFSCPolicyDetail
* updateFSCPolicyDetailGeneric
* postFSCPolicyTransaction
* getFSCPolicyRevenue
* updateFSCPolicyRevenue
* postFSCPolicyRevenue
* CancelPolicyRevenue
* GetInsurancePolicy

To add these Data Mappers and custom classes to your org, see Add Insurance Industries Extension Data Mappers and Custom Classes to Your Org.

If the provided Data Mappers and custom classes don't work for your business needs, you can write your own custom classes to work with the InsPolicy interface. See Create Custom Classes for the InsPolicy Interface.
title: Vlocity Insurance Integration with Salesforce
